    "Dilated fundus examination revealed a 270-degree right optic disc swelling without disc hemorrhage or pallor.",
    "The afferent and efferent examination of the left eye was normal.61-year-old male presented for the evaluation of new-onset horizontal double vision beginning three days prior to presentation.He reported that the double vision worsened when looking to his right.",
    "He denied any preceding injury, illness, or associated symptoms, such as numbness or weakness.",
    "However, he did note intermittent right-sided tinnitus for one month and mild swelling and tenderness behind his right ear beginning two days prior to presentation.",
    "His past medical history was significant for systemic hypertension, hyperlipidemia, and type 2 diabetes."
